sections.title: How the population has changed in Falkirk
sections.label: Select another local authority

sections.content: In 2020, Falkirk was the 11th largest local authority in Scotland, with a total population of 160,560. A decrease compared with 2019.

sections.title: Population density in Falkirk
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Falkirk was 540 people per square kilometre, which was more than Scotland (70), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Median age in Falkirk
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Falkirk was 44 years, which was older than Scotland (42 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
